original_font_information.description: Leslie Cabarga turned to the geometric, streamlined scripts prepared by American industrial designers for the inspiration of this series. In its three variation of letter spacing, Magneto recalls the chrome-strip lettering laid along the rounded shapes of refrigerator doors and automobile trunks in the forties and fifties; FB 1995.
